The paper deals with the problem of information transfer and distributed function computation in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science subfields. However, given the focus on wireless communication and networking, as well as the use of information theory to design efficient strategies, it is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Other relevant sub-categories include Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), and Machine Learning (cs.LG), as the paper touches upon aspects of these fields as well.
